  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: bug-monorepo (npm)",
  "details": "Bug-monorepo@3.1.94 runs a preinstall hook that executes index.js, which collects system information (hostname, username, home directory, DNS servers, /etc/passwd, /etc/hosts, package.json) from the installer's machine and exfiltrates it via HTTPS POST to cp5uzinglyy3ifb8gvvgvq5qvh19p0dp[.]oastify[.]com (a Burp Collaborator endpoint). The data is sent as a JSON payload over port 443.",
